<div id="apple-mdm" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">
      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="hero-row">
          <div purpose="page-hero-content">
            <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
              <h4>Apple Device Management</h4>
              <h1>Open source Apple MDM for modern IT and security teams</h1>
            </div>
            <div purpose="page-hero-text">
              <p>Enroll, configure, and secure Mac, iPhone, and iPad at enterprise scale. Manage Apple alongside Windows, Linux, Android, and ChromeOS in one place.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="button-row">
              <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
              <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a purpose="hero-quote" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jckwhet/" target="_blank" no-icon>
            <div purpose="hero-quote-profile-image">
              <img alt="Wes Whetstone, Client Platform Engineer at Stripe" src="/images/homepage-hero-wes-whetstone-86x72@2x.png">
            </div>
            <div purpose="quote-author-info">
              <p purpose="quote-text">“I just moved 10,000 Macs to Fleet”</p>
              <p purpose="quote-author-name">Wes Whetstone</p>
              <p purpose="quote-author-title">Client Platform Engineer at Stripe</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div purpose="hero-logos">
          <logo-carousel></logo-carousel>
        </div>
      </div><%/* landing-page-hero */%>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Traditional Apple MDM is holding IT back</h3>
          <p>Most Mac management tools were built for the desk-bound era. They make distributed Apple fleets harder to enroll, harder to audit, and harder to keep compliant.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="four-column-feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Vendor lock-in</h5>
            <p>Proprietary tools trap configurations behind GUIs, with steep renewals and limited export.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Manual ClickOps</h5>
            <p>Changes happen in a console with no version history. One bad profile breaks Wi-Fi for everyone.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Apple-only silos</h5>
            <p>Mac-only platforms force IT to run separate tools for Windows and Linux, with separate inventories.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Stale reporting</h5>
            <p>Periodic scans miss real-time compliance gaps that auditors and security teams need to see.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet showing Apple devices being managed at scale." src="/images/fleet-mdm-hero-1006x595@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>Manage Macs with the visibility and control modern IT teams need</h3>
            <p>Fleet is open source Apple device management built on Apple's native MDM protocol, Declarative Device Management (DDM), and Apple Business Manager. Configure, secure, and patch every Mac in your fleet without giving up transparency or cross-platform support.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Zero-touch enrollment through Apple Business Manager and Automated Device Enrollment.</p>
              <p>Enforce FileVault, configuration profiles, and DDM declarations from version-controlled YAML.</p>
              <p>Patch macOS, install Fleet-maintained apps, and run remediation scripts on demand.</p>
              <p>Continuously evaluate CIS Benchmarks for macOS and surface vulnerabilities in real time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <div purpose="quote-image">
            <img alt="Foursquare logo" src="/images/social-proof-logo-foursquare-170x32@2x.png">
          </div>
          <p purpose="quote-text">"Thanks for a great run Jamf. Foursquare has officially completed the migration to Fleet as our new device management platform. We're excited about how this move positions us to better support our teams."</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <div purpose="quote-author-image">
              <img alt="Mike Meyer" src="/images/testimonial-author-mike-meyer-48x48@2x.png">
            </div>
            <div purpose="name-and-title">
              <p purpose="author-name">Mike Meyer</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Senior systems engineer & Technical lead</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Foursquare</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Built for Apple-first teams</h2>
          <p>Whether you manage 500 MacBooks or 50,000, Fleet gives Mac admins the depth Apple deserves and the cross-platform reach the rest of the business needs.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Apple Business Manager integration</h5>
            <p>Connect ABM to Fleet and ship MacBooks directly to employees. Devices self-enroll the first time they power on.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Zero-touch deployment</h5>
            <p>Configure devices wirelessly with Automated Device Enrollment. Apps, profiles, and bootstrap packages install during Setup Assistant.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Declarative Device Management</h5>
            <p>Use Apple's modern DDM protocol so devices self-correct drift and report status asynchronously, even on slow links.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>FileVault disk encryption</h5>
            <p>Enforce FileVault, escrow recovery keys, and verify encryption status across every Mac from one dashboard.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>macOS software and patching</h5>
            <p>Deploy Fleet-maintained apps, App Store apps, and custom packages. Self-service installs keep users moving without tickets.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Live reports for every Mac</h5>
            <p>Powered by osquery, Fleet surfaces hardware, software, and security posture in seconds, not on the next inventory cycle.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>CIS Benchmarks for macOS</h5>
            <p>Run the complete macOS CIS Benchmark out of the box. Track compliance continuously and remediate with policies.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Scripts and remediation</h5>
            <p>Run shell scripts on Macs from the Fleet UI or API. Trigger fixes automatically when a policy fails.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>iOS and iPadOS, too</h5>
            <p>Enroll iPhones and iPads in user or supervised mode. Manage profiles, apps, and lost mode from the same console.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>GitOps and AI-ready Apple device management</h3>
            <p>Every Fleet configuration is a file. Store your profiles, policies, scripts, and software in your own Git repository. Review device changes the way you review code, ship them through CI, and roll back with a single revert.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Version-controlled configuration profiles, DDM declarations, and policies in YAML.</p>
              <p>Peer-review device changes in pull requests before they reach production.</p>
              <p>Generate Fleet config with any LLM, from ChatGPT and Claude to private models.</p>
              <p>Audit history, rollback, and CI/CD for your entire Apple estate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet running scripts and reports on a Mac." src="/images/linux-management-feature-image-scripts-504x378@2x.png">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Self-hosted, Fleet-hosted, or air-gapped</h2>
          <p>Run Fleet wherever your security and compliance teams need it, with the same features either way. Your device data stays inside your network.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Open source core</h5>
            <p>Fleet is MIT-licensed open source. Read the code, audit how Macs are managed, and adapt it to your needs.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Run it where you want</h5>
            <p>Deploy Fleet on AWS, Azure, GCP, your own data center, or use Fleet Cloud with 100% feature parity.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>One console, every platform</h5>
            <p>See macOS, iOS, iPadOS, Windows, Linux, Android, and ChromeOS in one inventory and one policy engine.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>API-first by design</h5>
            <p>Every feature in the Fleet UI is available over the REST API. Integrate with Okta, Jira, Slack, Snowflake, and your SIEM.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Smooth migration from Jamf</h5>
            <p>Use Apple's native MDM migration so users keep working. Fleet offers free migration support for qualifying teams.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Built with the Mac admin community</h5>
            <p>Fleet's contributors are practicing Mac admins. New macOS releases are supported on day one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What Mac admins are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>
  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">

    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Apple Device Management</h4>
        <h2>Modern, open source MDM for every Mac</h2>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
          <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
